        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1386415690,
        "creation_date": 1386415690,
        "body": "<p>You probably missed page/request lifecycle. If you require user to log in use AuthenticatedWebApplication instead and annotation based strategy.  <\/p>\n\n<p>If you throws RestartResponseAtInterceptPageException directly you could implement a wrong condition when to throw that exception. E.g. if you is not signed in, throw the exception, if the user is already signed (it is usually a flag in session), do not throw the exception.<\/p>\n\n<p>See authentication examples on <a href=\"http://www.wicket-library.com/wicket-examples-6.0.x/index.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://www.wicket-library.com/wicket-examples-6.0.x/index.html<\/a> <\/p>\n",
        "answer_id": 20440804,
